title: kokkuri-san_(gugukoku)
body:
Titular character of [i][[Gugure! Kokkuri-san]][/i].

He is a [[kitsune]] summoned by [[Ichimatsu Kohina]].  As a human, he has [[long hair|long]] [[silver hair]] and [[fox ears]].  He can also appear as a much smaller, fluffier red [[fox]].  In either form, he wears a giant [[bell]] on a rope with [i][[shide]][/i] around his neck.  

Kokkuri-san, in spite of being the male lead of the story, plays more of a motherly role towards Kohina.  He is frequently seen in an [[apron]], cooking, cleaning, and fussing over the small details for Kohina's house.  While [[inugami_(gugukoku)|Inugami]] uses guns for weapons, Kokkuri-san uses a [[frying pan]] as his weapon of choice to underline his domestic nature.  

Voiced by [[Ono Daisuke]].

title: inugami_(gugukoku)
body:
A major character of [i][[Gugure! Kokkuri-san]][/i].

(S)he is a gender-bending dog spirit who declares shimself the stalker of [[Ichimatsu Kohina]].  Inugami says this "allows either the yuri route or the normal route" for their love.  (Inugami is more often than not male in the actual story, but expect far more female images than male ones in the fanart...)

(S)he has [[short hair|short]] dark [[blue_hair|blue]]/[[purple hair]] with [[hair over one eye]], [[dog ears]], a lighter purple [[tail]], and has [[red eyes]].  (S)he usually wears a [[suit]] with a red [[armband]] and a [[necktie]].

title: ichimatsu_kohina
body:
One of the main characters of [i][[Gugure! Kokkuri-san]][/i]. She refers to herself as a "Mascot-type Heroine".

She proclaims herself a living doll, and speaks in an expressionless monotone with few facial expressions, although she gesticulates wildly to portray emphasis.  She lives alone, other than with the ghosts that haunt the place where she lives before she invites Kokkuri-san to also haunt her. She is also a cup noodle addict.

She has [[short hair|short]] [[black hair]] in a [[bob cut]] with [[straight bangs]] and has [[green eyes]].  She is usually seen wearing a [[school uniform]]. She is tiny, and often portrayed in [[chibi]] fashion.

title: yam_(dioscorea)
body:
A plant commonly cultivated for food. The tubers are edible, but some varieties must be prepared properly or the sap will cause poisoning. A common symptom of yam poisoning is itchiness when in contact with the skin and mouth, but certain varieties can cause paralysis or even death.

Not to be confused with [[sweet potato]]es, which is called yam in certain places.

title: rinka_lynx
body:
"[i]A sniper whose legendary skills have left battlefields littered with headless robots. A shadow of a grimace clouds her face as she levels her heavy support rifle.[/i]"
-Rinka Lynx's in-game description.

"[i]A legendary sniper known as "The Reaper." She carries a highly modified [Super Durable Guitar Case] bought at Maril's Music Store. Talk about killer riffs.[/i]"
-MR's in-game description.

"[i]A combination of proximity mines and unerring aim have made Rinka into a fearsome huntress. Those lucky enough to escape her first attack are quickly tracked down and dispatched.[/i]"
-BR's in-game description.

An ART bot, Rinka Lynx is a grey-haired [[Mecha Musume]] from the game [[Cosmic Break]] with an unique gameplay. Her sniper rifle allows for a scope zoom with varying magnifications, making her the ART with the longest reach in all the game. This is somewhat downplayed by her limit of 3 shots per time, although a lucky player may be able to cripple the target with them.

Rinka Lynx was originally a Garapon Bot, however two variations of her were added to the shop: a orange-haired version with 3 Tune-Up slots per part and a black-haired version with a single slot per part. Those two, while their stats are identical to those of the original, come with an incredibly nerfed Sniper Rifle, rendering her sniper gameplay pratically useless. However, all her sniper rifles can be swapped between her variations, therefore a player with an useless rifle can swap her with another more useful one if he manages to obtain another Rinka variation but doesn't wishes to swap robots.

Since Rinka was released alongside [[Kururu Gradd]], Kururu is often seen as Rinka's "Partner Bot", much like [[Melfi]] and [[Elisalotte]], even though they have no storyline together, or storylines at all. Their only connection, which in itself is still questionable, is Kururu's "Rinka Chainsaw" Wonder Bit.

title: yamabuki_inori
body: A 14-year-old schoolgirl at Christian Private White Clover Academy in [[Fresh Precure!]]. She is an animal lover, aspiring to be a veterinarian. Love tends to call her "Buki", the diminutive of her family name. She may look calm and quiet, but actually suffers from low self-esteem. In order to improve herself, she joins the dancing group with Love. She sometimes lacks common sense and just goes with whatever situation she finds herself in. Her hair is a golden orange colour that brightens to rusty blonde in cure form. Her Pickrun, the Kirun, is yellow and has horns on its head. Pine's theme colours are yellow and orange and her symbol is the diamond.

title: sarah_crewe
body:
The titular character and main protagonist of [[Princess Sarah]], who is brought to Miss Minchin's seminary in London to learn how to be a proper lady, after being raised in Bombay, India. Due to being pampered and doted on her entire life, Sarah's knowledge of the real world is limited, but she is still a friendly and imaginative girl. After her father dies and she is left destitute, Miss Minchin forces Sarah to work as a servant in the seminary, but Sarah instead pretends that she is a princess inside; while not looking as one. She refuses to lose hope and remains thoughtful and compassionate.

Voiced by: [[Shimamoto Sumi]]

title: princess_sarah
body:
Princess Sarah, also known as Little Princess Sara(h), is a 1985 Japanese anime series produced by Nippon Animation and Aniplex, based on Frances Hodgson Burnett's novel, A Little Princess.
Spanning 46 episodes, it originally premiered in 1985 across Japan on Fuji Television as the 11th series of Nippon Animation's World Masterpiece Theater.

It was also aired in numerous countries worldwide and translated into several languages, including French, Italian, German, Arabic, Filipino and Spanish.

title: janne_d'arc
body:
[b]Janne D'Arc[/b] is a character from the [[World Heroes]] series. 

Janne is a [[sword]]swoman from 15th century France. A bearer of a tremendous beauty and battle skill, she roamed her land in search of a strong fighter to become her husband, to no avail. However, she continues her search in different time periods now. 

She was born in France in April 5, 1412.

The character is loosely based on the legendary French national heroine, [[Jeanne d'Arc]] (Joan of Arc). However, Janne is more cocky than virtuous.

body:
A hanging scroll, called by the generic terms 立軸 ([i]lìzhóu[/i]) in China and 掛軸/掛け軸 ([i]kakejiku[/i]) in Japan, is an illustration or piece of [[calligraphy]] affixed to a [[scroll]] of cloth or paper.

When hanging scrolls first took their modern form during the "Northern Song Dynasty":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Song_Dynasty%23Northern_Song.2C_960.E2.80.931127&rct=j&q=Northern+Song+Dynasty&usg=AFQjCNFIrrx4svMf0c5D1xR1PQ26uXs3XQ&sa=X&ei=4IjqTrWKL-edmQWm_oWdCg&ved=0CDMQygQwAA of China, they were strongly characterized as portable murals to be used in religious ceremonies, but later came to be appreciated as art objects.

In the "Japanese Way of Tea,":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japanese_tea_ceremony these scrolls are called 掛物 ([i]kakemono[/i]), and are emphasized as an indispensable piece of equipment for the [[tea ceremony]]. Japanese [i]kakejiku[/i] are typically displayed in a special alcove for art objects called the "[i]tokonoma[/i].":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tokonoma

title: asterios
body: Asterios is a persona from the persona 4 arena game(s). He appears as a gigantic minotaur-like monster that is partially submerged in the ground, his head appears to be a large skull of a bull with metal attachments, chains, and partially sawed off horns that spew a reddish fire from the gouged out core. His body is mostly submerged, but appears to be a muscular humanoid that is colored black and is covered in chains that tie him to the earth, as well as having bone covered fists that he uses to beat his enemies to a pulp. Asterios is the persona of Shadow Labrys, although this fact is occasionally debated, as shadows (excluding Teddie) don't have Personas, only transformations into symbolic monsters, thus, Asterios is thought to be a mere extension of Shadow Labrys herself and symbolizes Labrys's desire for destruction.

title: myon_(phrase)
body:
A nonsensical catchphrase and nickname for [[Konpaku Youmu]] of [[Touhou]] fame.

The origin of the word is a line in the story for the EX stage in [[Perfect Cherry Blossom]] (included with the game in omake.txt). Youmu says at one point, "幽々子様！また、みょんな所に居て・・・" ("[[Saigyouji Yuyuko|Yuyuko-sama]]! Mata, myon na tokoro ni ite..."). The somewhat stilted Touhou wiki translation for this is "Lady Yuyuko! What are you doing in such a myon place...". "Myon na" here is a non-standard word Youmu uses, probably a mangling of two words for "strange", "myou na" and "hyon na", but not further explained by ZUN. This stuck as a very popular nickname for Youmu.

h4. See also

title: mialy
body:
"[i]Created many great inventions in an effort to overtake her childhood friend Rouche. After much blood, sweat, and tears, she has finally succeeded in developing the Pursuit Bit.[/i]"
 -Mialy's in-game description.

"[i]In spite of her recent success, Mialy still continues her hard work as an inventor. She has modified her weapons again in another attempt to best her rival, Rouche.[/i]"
 -Type.X's in-game description.

"[i]Mialy, who hates to lose, works harder than anyone else. As her rival and junior have both been improving, she's been frantically developing new inventions.[/i]"
 -Type.H's in-game description.

"[i]In the spirit of Halloween, Mialy has equipped pursuit bits with a cat motif. She put her pride into making them after being asked to help with the event.[/i]"
 -HW's in-game description.

"[i]Mialy created a special bouquet-shaped weapon and chose a dress to match it. The classic appearance of her Organdy train matches the miniskirt she chose almost too well.[/i]"
 -WD's in-game description.

"[i]Between her constant traveling between dimensions for press conferences and lectures, Mialy always finds time for her inventions. She's incorporated her research into her weaponry.[/i]"
 -Type.T's in-game description.

A Garapon [[Mecha Musume]] from the game [[Cosmic Break]], Mialy is an inventor who, like [[Rouche]], has an incredibly competitive personality. In-game, Mialy is an Artillery Bot introduced in the Inventor Gara with a cat theme and obviously focused in fan-service, with long, red hair tied in [[twintails]] and thin clothes that barely cover her chest and leave her panties exposed.

Mialy and Rouche are constantly trying to outsmart each other by building the best weapons, although their competition apparently always ends in a draw. Mialy focuses on powerful railguns and Pursuit Bits, portable railguns whose purpose is to follow and eliminate designed enemies without endangering the user. Her constant inventions resulted in 6 alternate versions in-game with different, but similar, weapons: Type.X, Type.H, HW, WD and Type.T.

Some time after Mialy invented her Type.X weapons, she met [[Illumis]], a young inventor who viewed her as a role model, and who soon improved so much along with Rouche that Mialy, struggling to keep up, built Type.H. Soon, Illumis also joined the competition, being on par with Rouche and Mialy, but also helped Mialy when possible, leading to several breakthroughs, as stated in Illumis' Type.Q's description.

title: maria_(hayate_no_gotoku!)
body:
Second female main character of [[Hayate no Gotoku!]]

[[Sanzen'in Nagi]]'s seventeen-year-old personal maid and colleague to her butler [[Ayasaki Hayate]]. Maria is a prodigy who graduated from Hayate and Nagi's school four years prior, and also acts as Nagi's mother figure. While caring and insightful (being aware of Nagi's one-sided affection for Hayate), she is deathly afraid of cockroaches and is extremely defensive about her age (itself ambiguous, as she was originally an orphan found as an infant next to a statue of the Virgin Mary, after whom she was named).

title: whom_dwell_in_vanity_(elona)
body:
([i]Kokuu wo Haizuru Mono[/i])

A side-character of the game [[Elona]], he is a disgraced former general in hiding. 

He's most known for being a shady loner type hanging around the graveyard that is in perpetual grief for his dead adopted sister, and for having the [[sword]] Ragnarok, which randomly causes an apocalypse if he gets into combat. This tends leading to some absurd/humorous/horrifying situations where Vernis, the town he is in at the start of the game, gets randomly destroyed by pillars of flames and epic [[dragon]] invasions because Whom Dwell In Vanity saw a mouse he didn't like or something.  

He joins in the group following [[Larnneire]], the [[elf|Elea]] Listener of Wind, as she tries to save the world while the player goes off to do random unrelated things as part of the main plot of [[Elona]].  

He wears a brown [[hooded_cloak]] covering most of his features, and, of course, has a sword.

title: freudia_neuwahl
body:
[[Spiritia_Rosenberg|Spiritia Rosenberg]]'s good, childhood friend, after which they've both known each other since they were children. Freudia is a calm and collected young woman who prefers to work alone. A lone wolf by nature, she is able to get things done without anyone's assistance. Despite not liking to be close to others, however, she shares a sister-like relationship with her. Her friends call her "Freu" for short.

Her weapon is Freudenstachel, which lets her quickly and rapidly fire icicles at opponents. In [[Rosenkreuzstilette Freudenstachel]], where she is the star of the game, she can learn different techniques of hers from every boss she defeats.

title: rilian_the_dog_lover
body:
Rilian the Dog Lover, (a mistranslation, since it's almost certainly meant to be "Lilian",) is an early-game quest NPC in [[Elona]].  She asks the player to find the lost puppy named Poppy in the Puppy Cave, an early-game dungeon.  

She and her quest are an homage to an early mission in the game [[ADOM]], with her taking the place of "Tiny Girl".

She has short, [[blue hair]], and wears a [[blue dress]].

title: lomias_(elona)
body:
Lomias, the Messenger From Vindale is one of the two first characters the player meets in the game [[Elona]], alongside his partner, [[Larnneire]], the Listener of Wind.  

He is a smug [[elf|elea]] who plays pranks on the player even while supposedly giving the game's tutorial. (Telling the player to eat the meat of a human beggar, which will cause sanity damage.  In a meta-game sense, this is to inform the player of the dangers of eating humanoid corpses.) Many players enjoy murdering him repeatedly for revenge. (He respawns infinitely when he reappears in specific events, and drops a unique bow.)

He has short [[green hair]], [[blue eyes]], pointed ears, and wears a loose blue-green [[jacket]].
